1 WHEREAS, birdwatching is an economic driver in the State of
2 Oklahoma and is a fun, relaxing, multigenerational, educational and
3 wellness activity for all; and
4 WHEREAS, a wide diversity of birds in Oklahoma indicates a
5 healthy environment; and
6 WHEREAS, Oklahoma is part of the central flyway through which
7 approximately 400 different species of birds migrate during the
8 spring and fall; and
9 WHEREAS, the Oklahoma state bird, the scissor-tailed flycatcher,
10 is one of the many species of birds that migrate to our state to
11 nest and rear their young; and
12 WHEREAS, most birds migrate at night, navigate by using the
13 stars and moon, and can become disoriented by bright artificial
14 light and sky glow, resulting in exhaustion and deadly collisions
15 with buildings, glass, power lines, and vehicles; and
16 WHEREAS, collisions with buildings is one of the top causes of
17 mortality of birds in the United States; and
18 WHEREAS, the Lights Out Oklahoma program strategy is aimed to
19 persuade building owners and managers and homeowners to turn off
20 exterior lighting on all buildings at night during the high
21 migration intensity months of April, May, September and October; and
22 WHEREAS, these measures save energy and money and protect birds
23 migrating to nesting grounds in the spring and wintering grounds in
24 the fall; and
