4 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
5 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
6 CONCURRING THEREIN:
7 THAT the Oklahoma State Legislature supports reducing bird
8 mortality in the areas and encourages Oklahoma businesses, state
9 agencies, organizations, and residents to turn off any exterior
10 lighting during the high migration intensity months of April, May,
11 September and October.
